    "extras": [
      "Intercity buses are strong for Larnaca, Nicosia, Limassol and Paphos, but they thin out in the evening and are weak for deeper Troodos village-hopping.",
      "Use OSYPA day passes in Paphos when you want to stitch together Tombs of the Kings, the harbour and Coral Bay-side routes without parking stress.",
      "Rent a car for one or two days specifically for Troodos and Cape Greco if you want scenic stops; remember Cyprus drives on the left.",
      "Tombs of the Kings, Kourion and Kykkos Museum are among the best-value paid sights on the island, so keep small cash or a working card handy.",
      "For beaches, September and early October give you warm water with much softer crowds than August."
    ],
